Thank you to everyone who came out to celebrate Daddy’s Little Caddy! We are so thankful for the love and support from the best friends and family! #BabyG 🍼✨💙

Blessed, excited, anxious, scared. 💙✨😊
.
We’ve felt every emotion but the overwhelming one is LOVE. Gordon and I have had so many amazing adventures together as a couple + now we can’t wait to make memories with our Baby G. 

Carrying this little love around with me has healed me in ways I didn’t even know I needed. He’s taught me things I didn’t know I needed to learn. Patience, courage, how to overcome fears, to slow down, to lean on those around me + so much more. I can’t imagine all the things he will teach us when we get to meet him in just 8 more weeks. 

Thank you to our family and friends for the advice, love, guidance, gifts + support. We feel it so much and can’t wait to share this journey with you. 🥹 Mama Lindley coming soon + and I know my heart will fall even more in love with Gor when I see him as a daddy. My 🤍can’t wait! 

#BabyG #GulledgeAdventures #32Weeks

James Gordon Gulledge IV “Ford” is an angel on earth! Stealing our hearts since 3:46pm on March 30th, 2023! 💙🍼

One week with Baby Ford IV 🫶

This has already been the most transformative time of my life. Every little smile or scrunch of the nose makes my heart melt a little more. It’s amazing to me that I get to be your mom. You exposed the scary unknown and taught me I can face my fears. The nights are long and the years will be fast + I can’t wait to watch who you will become. And don’t get me started on your daddy. Seeing @gordongull become a dad has made me fall more than I thought was possible. Thanks for catching my tears, for encouraging me + for being my best friend. #FORDIV

One month with our little love 🫶

Ford, I never knew what being a mama would feel like. You’ve taught me more in one month than I’ve learned in my lifetime so far. Your smiles and sweet snuggles seem to have slowed me down. Taught me that little moments are more important than small things on my many to do lists. You taught me not to wait for everything to make sense. You’ve changed this “type A” girl into a “live in each moment” type of girl. It’s been the hardest month of our lives with many sleepless nights, googling our biggest fears at 3am, questioning if we are doing everything right and adjusting to our new “normal.” But somehow all of that fades away when you grab my finger with your tiny little hand. Thank you for making me a mama. ☝️month down + forever to go. Love you JGG IV. ✨
#FordIV

🕊️Barbara Anne Lindley Kitchen🕊️ 

November 13th, 1938 - December 31st, 2023

My sweet meme gained her Angel wings on New Year’s Eve. Our hearts are broken but our faith is strong and we know she is rejoicing in Heaven. 

Her love for God and others, her welcoming smile and her steadfast faith made her the most special person. She did not meet a stranger and would do anything for her family and friends. She loved beautiful things, my momma, her grandchildren and my sweet Papa with all her heart. She was selfless, loving, giving and will surely have a crown in heaven full of jewels for her devotion! 

Her and Papa’s loving relationship inspired Gordon and I every single day. I am so grateful that she got to see my precious Ford come into this world. He smiled so big every time he saw her and I know he could feel her  love. 

Meme, Thank you for your sacrifices, your care and concern, your love and everything that you have done for me. I cannot think of a more amazing woman to be named after and I promise to always strive to make you proud. Your memories will live on within us forever. We will miss you every day and we love you, always!!! 

I will post details about the arrangements as soon as we have them for those who would like to come honor my sweet Meme and celebrate her life with us. Thank you for all of the prayers and love. We have felt it all and appreciate all of you.
My little FORD man! 🫶✨💙

Happy Birthday to my person 🫶 
.
.
I’ve known you for over half my life + loved you just as long. Life is such an adventure with you. Each year brings more + more laughter + memories + this one brought us baby Ford. It wasn’t always easy but you’ve always made me feel like I could accomplish anything. You are the most perfect example of a loving husband + dad to our little man + you make me laugh every day. I am so proud of who you are + so grateful to be your wife. I can’t wait to see what this year holds + have all the dances we can. I love you!

💃🏻Owner @shockdancebylindley + @crowncouturecollection
💍Mrs. Gulledge
